# This file is SYSTEM: it is a template, and an update replaces it.
#
# Your real config lives in your WORKING FOLDER, at <workspace>/.env — created for you on
# first run, and never touched by an update. Find it with:  ./run.sh where
#
# The only reason to put a .env HERE is to set something that must be known before the
# working folder can even be located: in practice just MANAGER_WORKSPACE or MANAGER_PYTHON.
# Anything exported in your shell beats both files.

# --- where things live -----------------------------------------------------
# The WORKING FOLDER: board state, cards and their folders, columns, worker prompts.
# Yours; never overwritten. Default: ~/.manager-kanban/<repo-name>/
# (MANAGER_DATA_DIR is the older name for this and is still honoured.)
# MANAGER_WORKSPACE=/absolute/path/to/your/working-folder

# The repo the manager operates on. Default: the folder this system-folder sits in.
# MANAGER_REPO_DIR=/absolute/path/to/your/repo

# Where the worker prompts live. Default: <workspace>/workers
# MANAGER_WORKERS_DIR=

# The Python used to build the venv (3.10+ required). Default: the newest one on PATH.
# MANAGER_PYTHON=/opt/homebrew/bin/python3.12

# --- the manager -----------------------------------------------------------
# Live mode needs EITHER a key here OR a logged-in Claude Code CLI: the Agent SDK falls back
# to the CLI's OAuth session, so "no API key" has never actually meant "no live mode".
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Force the scripted mock manager (1) or the real one (0). Unset = auto-detect — and the
# server prints which one it chose and exactly why.
# MANAGER_MOCK=

# MANAGER_PORT=4173                            board port; bound to 127.0.0.1 only
# MANAGER_MODEL=                               e.g. claude-opus-4-8, claude-sonnet-5
# MANAGER_PERMISSION_MODE=bypassPermissions    default | acceptEdits | bypassPermissions
